'''Jadwiga Łopata''', is an organic farmer living near [[Cracow]], [[Poland]]. She was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2002, for her works on rural protection.<ref name="goldman">Goldman Environmental Prize: [http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/125 Jadwiga Lopata] (Retrieved on November 10, 2007)</ref> She is co-founder and co-director of the ''International Coalition to Protect the Polish Countryside'' (ICPPC).

