'''PTFE Structured Packing''' refers to a range of specially designed materials for use in [[absorption (chemistry)|absorption]] and [[Fractionating column|distillation columns]] and [[chemical reactor]]s. [http://reprap.org/wiki/PTFE PTFE] [[Structured packing]] typically consist of thin corrugated [[Polytetrafluoroethylene|PTFE Sheets]] <ref>{{cite web|title=PTFE Packing Materials|url= http://www.ptfepacking.net/|publisher=American Seal and Packing |work=ptfepacking.net|date=28 February 2015|accessdate=16 Feb 2015}}</ref> arranged in a way that they force [[fluid]]s to take complicated paths through the column, thereby creating a large surface area for contact between different [[Phase (matter)|phases]].

