{{Chembox | Verifiedfields = changed | Watchedfields = changed | verifiedrevid = 477171798 | Reference = <ref name="hand"> {{Citation | last = Lide | first = David R. | year = 1998 | title = Handbook of Chemistry and Physics | edition = 87 | publication-place = Boca Raton, Florida | publisher = CRC Press | isbn = 0-8493-0594-2 | pages = 4–76}}</ref> | ImageFile = Kristallstruktur Uran(IV)-fluorid.png | IUPACName = Plutonium(IV) fluoride | OtherNames = Plutonium tetrafluoride |Section1={{Chembox Identifiers | Abbreviations = | CASNo_Ref = {{cascite|changed|??}} | CASNo = 13709-56-3 | PubChem = 139558 | StdInChI_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}} | StdInChI = 1S/4FH.Pu/h4*1H;/q;;;;+3/p-4 | StdInChIKey_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}} | StdInChIKey = OHWOGGZFHLFRES-UHFFFAOYSA-J | ChemSpiderID_Ref = {{chemspidercite|correct|chemspider}} | ChemSpiderID =14074494}} |Section2={{Chembox Properties | Formula = PuF<sub>4</sub> | MolarMass = 320 g/mol | Appearance = reddish-brown [[monoclinic]] crystals | Density = 7.1 g/cm<sup>3</sup> | MeltingPtC = 1027 | MeltingPt_notes = | BoilingPt = | BoilingPt_notes = | Solubility = | SolubleOther = | Solvent = | pKa = | pKb = }} |Section3={{Chembox Structure | CrystalStruct = [[Monoclinic]], [[Pearson symbol|mS60]] | SpaceGroup = C12/c1, No. 15 }} |Section7={{Chembox Hazards | ExternalSDS = | EUClass = | MainHazards = | NFPA-H = | NFPA-F = | NFPA-R = | NFPA-S = | RPhrases = | SPhrases = | RSPhrases = | FlashPt = | AutoignitionPt = | ExploLimits = | PEL = }} }}
'''Plutonium(IV) fluoride''' is a chemical compound with the formula (PuF<sub>4</sub>). Like all [[plutonium]] compounds, it is subject to control under the [[Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty]].
Metallic plutonium is produced by reacting plutonium tetrafluoride with barium, calcium, or lithium at 1200&nbsp;°C:
:PuF<sub>4</sub> + 2 Ba → 2 BaF<sub>2</sub> + Pu :PuF<sub>4</sub> + 2 Ca → 2 CaF<sub>2</sub> + Pu :PuF<sub>4</sub> + 4 Li → 4 LiF + Pu
