{{infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Toms River: A Story of Science and Salvation | title_orig = | translator = | image = Toms River-A Story of Science and Salvation.jpg | border = yes | author = [[Dan Fagin]] | illustrator = | caption = | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = [[Environmental issues in the United States]], [[environmental science]], [[oncology]] | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = [[Bantam Books|Bantam]] | release_date = March, 2013 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover|Hardback]]) | pages = 560 | isbn = 978-0-553-80653-3 | dewey = 363.7209749/48 | congress = 2012-017030 | oclc = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Toms River: A Story of Science and Salvation''''' is a 2013 non-fiction book by the American author [[Dan Fagin]].<ref name=zuger>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/03/19/health/on-the-trail-of-cancer-a-review-of-toms-river-by-dan-fagin.html |title=On the Trail of Cancer |work=[[The New York Times]] |author=Abigail Zuger |date=March 18, 2013 |accessdate=April 17, 2014}}</ref> It is about the dumping of industrial pollution by chemical companies in [[Toms River, New Jersey]] beginning in 1952 through the 1980s,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newyorker.com/online/blogs/elements/2013/05/a-town-plagued-by-water.html |title=A Town Plagued by Water |work=[[The New Yorker]] |author=Alexander Nazaryan |date=May 24, 2013 |accessdate=April 17, 2014}}</ref> and the [[epidemiology|epidemiological]] investigations of a [[cancer cluster]] that subsequently emerged there. The book won the [[2014 Pulitzer Prize]] for [[Pulitzer Prize for General Non-Fiction|General Non-Fiction]],<ref name="general-non-fiction">{{Cite web|url=http://www.pulitzer.org/prize-winners-by-category/223|title=The Pulitzer Prizes: General Nonfiction|date=April 2014|accessdate=April 15, 2014|publisher=Pulitzer.org}}</ref> the 2014 [[Helen Bernstein Book Award for Excellence in Journalism]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nypl.org/help/about-nypl/awards/book-award-for-journalism/past-winners|title=Past Winners of The New York Public Library Helen Bernstein Book Award for Excellence in Journalism|publisher=[[New York Public Library]]|accessdate=February 21, 2017}}</ref> and the 2014 [[National Academies Communication Award]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.keckfutures.org/awards/2014winners.html|title=National Academies Keck Futures Initiative - - Communication Awards|publisher=}}</ref>
